---
// Standalone page — self-contained styles and scripts, no global.css
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Kentucky Veto Override | Bearing Freedom</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Kentucky legislature crushes Beshear's gun vetoes. HB 78 and HB 312 overridden with massive supermajorities. Full breakdown."
    />
    <meta
      property="og:title"
      content="Kentucky Veto Override | Bearing Freedom"
    />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Kentucky's legislature overrode Governor Beshear's vetoes on two pro-gun bills with massive supermajority votes. Full breakdown of HB 78 and HB 312."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://bearingfreedom.com/override" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <!-- GA4 -->
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-YJWJPMSXN4"
    ></script>
    <script is:inline>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag() {
        dataLayer.push(arguments);
      }
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', 'G-YJWJPMSXN4');
    </script>
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oswald:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style is:global>
      *,
      *::before,
      *::after {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }
      :root {
        --bg: #0a0a08;
        --surface: #12120f;
        --card: #1a1a16;
        --card-hover: #1e1e19;
        --gold: #d4a017;
        --gold-bright: #f0c040;
        --gold-dim: rgba(212, 160, 23, 0.12);
        --green: #22c55e;
        --green-dim: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1);
        --green-bright: #4ade80;
        --red: #dc2626;
        --red-dim: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.08);
        --blue: #3b82f6;
        --white: #f0ede6;
        --light: #d4d0c8;
        --dim: #a3a098;
        --muted: #6b6860;
        --faint: #3a3830;
        --border: #2a2820;
        --font: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
        --head: 'Oswald', sans-serif;
        --mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      }
      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }
      body {
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--white);
        font-family: var(--font);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        line-height: 1.7;
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      /* === TEXTURE OVERLAY === */
      body::before {
        content: '';
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        background: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)' opacity='0.03'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 9999;
      }

      /* === HEADER === */
      .site-header {
        background: var(--surface);
        border-bottom: 3px solid var(--gold);
        padding: 16px 32px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 100;
      }
      .site-header a {
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .header-brand {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 20px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--white);
      }
      .header-nav {
        display: flex;
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: center;
      }
      .header-nav a {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--dim);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: color 0.2s;
      }
      .header-nav a:hover {
        color: var(--gold);
      }

      /* === HERO === */
      .hero {
        position: relative;
        padding: 80px 32px 60px;
        text-align: center;
        background: linear-gradient(
          180deg,
          rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.06) 0%,
          transparent 60%
        );
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .hero::before {
        content: 'OVERRIDE';
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: clamp(120px, 18vw, 280px);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: 20px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.04);
        white-space: nowrap;
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .hero-state {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        display: inline-block;
      }
      .hero h1 {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 72px);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        line-height: 1.05;
        color: var(--white);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .hero h1 .green {
        color: var(--green);
      }
      .hero-sub {
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--dim);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto 32px;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      .hero-date {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--green);
        background: var(--green-dim);
        padding: 8px 20px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        display: inline-block;
        border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15);
      }

      /* === STATS BANNER === */
      .stats-banner {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 1px;
        background: var(--border);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .stat-cell {
        background: var(--surface);
        padding: 28px 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .stat-val {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 32px;
        font-weight: 800;
        color: var(--green);
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }
      .stat-val.gold {
        color: var(--gold);
      }
      .stat-val.red {
        color: var(--red);
      }
      .stat-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--muted);
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-top: 6px;
      }

      /* === CONTENT === */
      .content {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 60px 32px;
      }

      .section-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: 4px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 32px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--white);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        line-height: 1.15;
      }

      h3 {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--white);
        margin: 40px 0 16px;
      }

      p {
        color: var(--light);
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        font-size: 17px;
      }

      strong {
        color: var(--white);
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      /* === BILL CARDS === */
      .bill-card {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 32px;
        margin: 32px 0;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .bill-card::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 3px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--green), var(--gold));
      }
      .bill-id {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold);
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .bill-title {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 24px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--white);
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }
      .bill-sponsor {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--dim);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .bill-body {
        color: var(--light);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }

      /* === VOTE GRID === */
      .vote-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 12px;
        margin: 20px 0;
      }
      .vote-box {
        background: var(--green-dim);
        border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 16px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .vote-box.override {
        border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3);
      }
      .vote-chamber {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--dim);
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .vote-count {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 28px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--green);
      }
      .vote-label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        color: var(--green);
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-top: 4px;
      }

      /* === OVERRIDE BADGE === */
      .override-badge {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        background: var(--green-dim);
        border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
        color: var(--green);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        padding: 6px 14px;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }

      /* === QUOTE === */
      .quote-block {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
        padding: 20px 24px;
        margin: 28px 0;
        background: var(--gold-dim);
        border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      }
      .quote-text {
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 17px;
        color: var(--light);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      .quote-attr {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--muted);
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      /* === TIMELINE === */
      .timeline {
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 28px;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .timeline::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        left: 6px;
        top: 4px;
        bottom: 4px;
        width: 2px;
        background: var(--faint);
      }
      .tl-item {
        position: relative;
        padding: 0 0 20px 20px;
      }
      .tl-item::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        left: -24px;
        top: 7px;
        width: 10px;
        height: 10px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: var(--faint);
        border: 2px solid var(--bg);
      }
      .tl-item.major::before {
        background: var(--green);
        box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.4);
      }
      .tl-item.veto::before {
        background: var(--red);
        box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.4);
      }
      .tl-date {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--muted);
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }
      .tl-text {
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--light);
      }
      .tl-text strong {
        color: var(--green);
      }
      .tl-item.veto .tl-text strong {
        color: var(--red);
      }

      /* === CALLOUT === */
      .callout {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 24px 28px;
        margin: 28px 0;
      }
      .callout.red {
        border-color: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.2);
        background: var(--red-dim);
      }
      .callout.green {
        border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
        background: var(--green-dim);
      }
      .callout-title {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
      .callout.red .callout-title {
        color: var(--red);
      }
      .callout.green .callout-title {
        color: var(--green);
      }

      /* === DIVIDER === */
      .divider {
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--border);
        margin: 48px 0;
        position: relative;
      }
      .divider::after {
        content: attr(data-label);
        position: absolute;
        left: 50%;
        top: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        background: var(--bg);
        padding: 0 16px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--muted);
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      /* === TABLE === */
      .data-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 20px 0;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      .data-table th {
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--muted);
        text-align: left;
        padding: 10px 14px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
      }
      .data-table td {
        padding: 12px 14px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--light);
      }
      .data-table tr:last-child td {
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      .tag-green {
        background: var(--green-dim);
        color: var(--green);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 700;
        padding: 3px 8px;
        border-radius: 3px;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }
      .tag-red {
        background: var(--red-dim);
        color: var(--red);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 700;
        padding: 3px 8px;
        border-radius: 3px;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      /* === LOUISVILLE SECTION === */
      .lou-section {
        background: var(--surface);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding: 60px 32px;
        margin: 48px 0;
      }
      .lou-inner {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .reg-bar {
        display: flex;
        height: 18px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        overflow: hidden;
        margin: 16px 0 8px;
      }
      .reg-bar .dem {
        background: var(--blue);
        flex: 56;
      }
      .reg-bar .rep {
        background: var(--red);
        flex: 32;
      }
      .reg-bar .ind {
        background: var(--muted);
        flex: 12;
      }
      .reg-labels {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--dim);
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      /* === CTA === */
      .cta-section {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 60px 32px;
        background: linear-gradient(
          0deg,
          rgba(212, 160, 23, 0.06) 0%,
          transparent 80%
        );
      }
      .cta-section h2 {
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .cta-section p {
        color: var(--dim);
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }
      .cta-btn {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: var(--head);
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: #000;
        background: var(--gold);
        padding: 14px 36px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: all 0.2s;
      }
      .cta-btn:hover {
        background: var(--gold-bright);
        transform: translateY(-1px);
      }

      /* === FOOTER === */
      .site-footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 32px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--muted);
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }
      .site-footer a {
        color: var(--gold);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      /* === RESPONSIVE === */
      @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .stats-banner {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        }
        .vote-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        .hero {
          padding: 48px 20px 40px;
        }
        .content {
          padding: 40px 20px;
        }
        .bill-card {
          padding: 24px 20px;
        }
        .site-header {
          padding: 12px 16px;
        }
        .header-nav {
          gap: 12px;
        }
        .header-nav a {
          font-size: 10px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- HEADER -->
    <header class="site-header">
      <a href="/"><span class="header-brand">Bearing Freedom</span></a>
      <nav class="header-nav">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/legislation">VA Tracker</a>
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/@BearingFreedom?sub_confirmation=1"
          target="_blank">Subscribe</a
        >
      </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-state">Commonwealth of Kentucky</div>
      <h1>Beshear's Gun Vetoes<br /><span class="green">Crushed</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The Kentucky General Assembly overrode Governor Andy Beshear's vetoes on
        two major pro-gun bills with overwhelming supermajority votes. The
        Second Amendment won. Here's how it happened.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-date">Override sustained April 14, 2026</div>
    </section>

    <!-- STATS -->
    <div class="stats-banner">
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-val">2</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Bills Overridden</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-val">81-18</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Largest Override Vote</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-val red">32</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Beshear Vetoes in 2026</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-val gold">80-20</div>
        <div class="stat-label">GOP House Supermajority</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BILL 1 -->
    <div class="content">
      <div class="section-label">The Two Bills</div>
      <h2>What the legislature passed and the governor tried to kill</h2>

      <div class="bill-card">
        <div class="bill-id">HB 78</div>
        <div class="bill-title">
          Protection of Lawful Commerce in Arms Act of 2026
        </div>
        <div class="bill-sponsor">
          Rep. T.J. Roberts (R-Burlington) + 10 co-sponsors
        </div>
        <div class="bill-body">
          <p style="margin-bottom:12px">
            State-level liability protections for firearms manufacturers,
            distributors, and retailers against civil lawsuits arising from
            criminal or unlawful misuse of their products. Modeled after the
            federal PLCAA. Includes exceptions for negligence, federal law
            violations, and product defects. Preempts local firearms liability
            ordinances.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:0">
            This bill exists because anti-gun states have been passing laws
            designed to circumvent the federal PLCAA and weaponize the courts
            against the firearms industry. Kentucky said no.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:16px">
          <span class="override-badge">Override Sustained</span>
        </div>

        <div class="vote-grid">
          <div class="vote-box override">
            <div class="vote-chamber">House Override</div>
            <div class="vote-count">80-19</div>
            <div class="vote-label">Override sustained</div>
          </div>
          <div class="vote-box override">
            <div class="vote-chamber">Senate Override</div>
            <div class="vote-count">31-6</div>
            <div class="vote-label">Override sustained</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bill-card">
        <div class="bill-id">HB 312</div>
        <div class="bill-title">
          Provisional Concealed Carry for 18-20 Year Olds
        </div>
        <div class="bill-sponsor">
          Rep. Savannah Maddox (R-Dry Ridge) + 27 co-sponsors
        </div>
        <div class="bill-body">
          <p style="margin-bottom:12px">
            Authorizes Kentucky State Police to issue provisional concealed
            carry licenses to 18-20 year olds. Requires background check (state
            and federal), up to 8 hours of firearm safety training, and
            proficiency demonstration. Builds on Kentucky's 2019 constitutional
            carry law, which allows permitless concealed carry for those 21 and
            older.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:0">
            An 18-year-old can vote, serve in combat, and die for their country.
            Rep. Maddox made sure they can carry a firearm to protect themselves
            too.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:16px">
          <span class="override-badge">Override Sustained</span>
        </div>

        <div class="vote-grid">
          <div class="vote-box override">
            <div class="vote-chamber">House Override</div>
            <div class="vote-count">81-18</div>
            <div class="vote-label">Override sustained</div>
          </div>
          <div class="vote-box override">
            <div class="vote-chamber">Senate Override</div>
            <div class="vote-count">28-9</div>
            <div class="vote-label">Override sustained</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="divider" data-label="The Veto"></div>

      <div class="section-label">April 3, 2026</div>
      <h2>Beshear's justification</h2>

      <p>
        Governor Andy Beshear vetoed both bills on April 3, 2026. On HB 312, he
        argued minimum age limits "protect young people," pointing out that
        Kentuckians under 21 cannot rent a car, buy alcohol, or serve as a state
        lawmaker. On HB 78, he characterized the bill as prioritizing "immunity
        for gun dealers over the safety of the Commonwealth's citizens."
      </p>

      <p>
        For both vetoes, Beshear invoked <strong>Tommy Elliott</strong>, a
        personal friend killed in the April 10, 2023 Old National Bank mass
        shooting in Louisville. Elliott was a senior vice president at the bank
        and had chaired Beshear's 2019 inaugural committee.
      </p>

      <div class="callout red">
        <div class="callout-title">The real context</div>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">
          Families of the Old National Bank victims filed a lawsuit against
          River City Firearms, the store that legally sold the shooter a
          firearm. HB 78 is exactly the type of law designed to stop these
          politically motivated lawsuits that blame legal sellers for criminal
          actions. Beshear's vetoes weren't about safety. They were about
          protecting his allies' lawsuit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <div class="quote-text">
          "We don't sue Ford for drunk drivers. We shouldn't sue the 2A out of
          existence."
        </div>
        <div class="quote-attr">Rep. T.J. Roberts (R) on HB 78</div>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <div class="quote-text">
          "Firearm industry members are no more responsible for criminal actions
          than Kentucky's bourbon distillers are responsible for drunk driving
          deaths."
        </div>
        <div class="quote-attr">
          Lawrence Keane, NSSF Senior VP & General Counsel
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="divider" data-label="The Override"></div>

      <div class="section-label">April 14, 2026</div>
      <h2>The legislature spoke</h2>

      <p>
        Kentucky requires only a simple majority to override a veto (51 in the
        House, 20 in the Senate). Both bills blew past those thresholds. In the
        2026 session alone, Beshear issued <strong>32 total vetoes</strong>. The
        legislature overrode nearly all of them, sustaining only 3 small
        line-item budget vetoes.
      </p>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <div class="quote-text">
          "Who sets the priority of policy? Not the governor, not the Supreme
          Court. The General Assembly."
        </div>
        <div class="quote-attr">Senate President Robert Stivers (R)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="callout green">
        <div class="callout-title">Both bills are now law</div>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">
          HB 78 and HB 312 became law on April 14, 2026, the moment the override
          votes were sustained. The governor's vetoes are dead. Kentucky's
          firearm industry has state-level liability protections, and
          responsible 18-20 year olds can now obtain provisional concealed carry
          licenses.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3>Key voices</h3>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <div class="quote-text">
          "This measure recognizes that many responsible young adults already
          legally vote, sign contracts, join the military, serve in combat,
          start a family, own a business, and work in law enforcement fields,
          yet under current law, these adults are prohibited from carrying a
          firearm concealed for self-defense."
        </div>
        <div class="quote-attr">Rep. Savannah Maddox (R) on HB 312</div>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-block">
